[[# anchor-conprocs]]

**Special Containment Procedures:** Personnel interacting with SCP-001 directly must adhere to the following guidelines:



* When addressing SCP-001, it is to be referred to as “Seeress” at all times unless otherwise instructed. 

* Professionalism is expected in all interactions. 

* Movements in SCP-001’s presence must be slow and methodical. 

* Disciplinary measures to ensure SCP-001’s continued anomalous activity are unnecessary and actively detrimental. 

* Suggestions of punitive measures for undesired outcomes or inaccessible results are unacceptable. 

* Verbal abuse, threats, and acts of physical violence towards SCP-001 are also unacceptable. 

* Attempting to force SCP-001 to exert prescience without electronic assistance is //also// unacceptable.  



Failure to follow any of the above guidelines will result in revocation of access to the Silicon Nornir, SCP-001, and referral to the Ethics Committee for disciplinary review regardless of seniority, office, or internal standing. 



[[include <a href="/component:image-block">component:image-block</a> name= https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/bleep-s-onyx-proposal/Die_Nornen_Urd%252C_Werdanda%252C_Skuld%252C_unter_der_Welteiche_Yggdrasil_by_Ludwig_Burger.webp|align=right|caption=The Norns.]]



Utilization of SCP-001’s anomalous capabilities for all relevant purposes are restricted to Department Heads, Site Directors, the Ethics Committee, and the O5 Council unless explicit permission was received one year in advance. SCP-001, the Nornir, and Eurtec are remanded under O5-07’s domains of operation at this time. 



Researchers interested in conducting projects and initiatives involving SCP-001 are required to submit applications to join MTF Omega-77 as part of the broader Department of Prescience and Predictive Sciences. 



In the interest of maintaining the techno-thaumaturgic Nornir Cult and the Silicon Nornir’s Foresight Matrix Array’s operation, SCP-001 has been granted level-5 humanoid anomaly privileges. Level-5 privileges have continued since 1970 when the Foundation assumed operational command and control of Special Anomalous Free Port-03 (Eurtec) following the collapse of the GOC. These privileges are as follows: 



* A private residence within the greater city of Eurtec, free of active monitoring and/or containment measures in recognition of excellent behavior. 

* Freedom of mobility throughout Eurtec without armed escort. 

* Access to leisure activities upon request and within reason. 

* Disability accommodations for blindness. 

* Remote and direct access to monitored personal electronic equipment capable of interfacing with the Nornir Foresight Matrix Arrays at all times.

* Access to artistic and creative materials for Trojan Events where personal electronics are insufficient. 

* Approval for extra-Eurtec excursions accompanied by field and combat trained elements of MTF Omega-77 (“Fortune Tellers”) submitted with six months advanced notice.[[footnote]]Currently unused following SCP-001’s emotional and mental breakdown at Mount Helicon on May 5th, 2009.[[/footnote]]



The organizational structure[[footnote]] Including the Speaker and Priests tasked with helping interpret SCP-001’s anomalous capabilities.[[/footnote]] of the Silicon Nornir at the time of its absorption by the Foundation consisted of SCP-001 and what is now MTF Omega-77.[[footnote]]The larger organizational body of priests, technicians, and corporate workers who built and maintain the overall Nornir Complex.[[/footnote]] It is in the best interest of SCP-001’s anomalous capacities to continue to maintain this social structure.  



[[include <a href="/component:image-block">component:image-block</a> name=https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/bleep-s-onyx-proposal/Cassandra%2520Portrait.webp|width=400px|align=right|caption=SCP-001.]]



[[# anchor-description]]

**Description:** SCP-001 is both a single Class IX [[footnote]]Seer Goddess.[[/footnote]] humanoid prescient anomaly and a Class VIII [[footnote]]Goddess.[[/footnote]] reality-altering entity. The techno-thaumaturgic Nornir Cult believes SCP-001 to be the last surviving member of the Norns or Nornir.[[footnote]]Norse goddesses who control destiny.[[/footnote]] It is referred to by the Cult of the Nornir as “The Last Norn,” “The Seeress on High,” “Destiny’s Fingers,” or “Name Unspoken.” SCP-001 presents as a 1.79-meter-tall woman believed to be of Mediterranean descent which appears to be in its early thirties, with this appearance remaining in perpetuity due to its functional immortality. Notable bodily features include a utilitarian block-needle tattoo on its left arm reading “4444” and blindness.



SCP-001’s anomalous properties involve the onset of prescient “visions” which frequently occur at all times of the day, regardless of its stage of consciousness. It describes its abilities as “uncontrolled sight”, referred to as “Trojan Events”[[footnote]]In reference to Cassandra of Troy. Multiple names were put forward by research personnel and the Cult of the Nornir, but SCP-001 failed to react to all but the one chosen.[[/footnote]] by research personnel. These events consist of possible past, present, or future events of varying magnitudes and importance. Trojan Events are normally random, unfocused, and often undirected, though some specificity arises from contact with specific triggering items, topics, or words. Use of the Nornir Foresight Matrix Arrays (NFMA) [[footnote]]The triple skyscrapers and large complex at the center of Eurtec, where the skyscrapers serve as massive thaumaturgic computing cores.[[/footnote]] or exerted prescience can focus SCP-001’s capacities, but it prefers to avoid exerted prescience.



Continuous efforts are ongoing to maintain, replace, and increase the number of empathetic individuals with strong moral direction working with SCP-001 in order to improve its predictive capacity. 



Despite having been in Foundation remand for more than half a century, personal details regarding SCP-001 are sparse to nonexistent. Its true given name, if it has one, remains undisclosed.





