**PTE-001:** Lost in the threads of time and remembrance in an ancient place of forest and streams yet untouched by modern machinations. In simpler terms, I was a blind hermit living in mountain woods. Sometimes a fortune teller for young lovers and small children who came up to my cabin from the villages. It depended on the person who stepped into my abode. 



//Colonel Bowe looks down at the papers on the podium and stops smiling.//



**Colonel Bowe:** So, would you say you were a part of an occultic organization prior to your capture? 



//PTE-001 tilts its head. Now when it speaks it is less shaky than previously.//



**PTE-001:** No. Such things have not been appealing to me for a very long time.



**Colonel Bowe:** Strange, one would think a Norn as you are claimed to be, would be associated with a coven of sisters. Is this not the case?



//PTE-001 is still for several seconds before slowly tilting its head.//



**PTE-001:** I was with a coven of sisters of many natures, of fate, of thread and weave of man’s inspiration and make and yet not all the same. Tied and bound to the strands of destiny in ways both our own and yet not. 



**Colonel Bowe:** So, you were with the Norns? Why did you tell the committee you weren’t with an Occultic Organization?



**PTE-001:** They went by many names, but they were never a structured hierarchy of grand sprawl as mortals weave in modern days. 



//Colonel Bowe pinches the bridge of his nose.// 



**Colonel Bowe:** I’m certain that both my peers on the Committee and the Cult of the Nornir are aware that the Norns are very well characterized as beautiful women. If you would all please turn in your folders to the medical documentation, and read the report submitted by the staff at Oslo University Hospital.



//Several minutes of pages rustling and silence as all parties read the indicated documents. Cult of the Nornir representatives become visibly agitated.//



**Colonel Bowe:** Now, I don’t think anyone in this room will contest that PTE-001 is certainly beautiful. However; here in this medical report it indicates that PTE-001 possesses atypical anatomical features inconsistent with a woman. In other more direct terms, PTE-001 has male genitalia. Are you, in fact, a man, PTE-001? 



//PTE-001 sways in place and hunches its shoulders. Its voice becomes shaky again.//



**PTE-001:** No, I’m a woman.



**Colonel Bowe:** Even with the anatomic abnormality you possess? Don’t you think it’s a little odd? Just about all the perfect features, except for this one part. Maybe you’re ashamed of what they did to you? Maybe you’re a deviant, or maybe you’ve been struck with hysteria. 



//PTE-001 places one hand on the back of its neck. Its head is tilted down and its voice cracks when it speaks.//



**PTE-001:** No! I— 



**Speaker Ella:** I must object! How can you sit here and lecture us on what shape the divine might take? How can you know that they don’t take whichever forms they wish, no matter how strange they may seem? 



**Colonel Bowe:** That’s precisely my point, Speaker Ella. How can we know that the Norns, or any of the divine, will take the shapes we expect? Wouldn’t that open the door for our enemies? Or worse, open the doors for the very things we seek to prevent from destroying humanity to slip in? Would that not allow them to mime the very shapes we put our highest faith in? 



**Speaker Ella:** This is beyond the realm of speculative! How is any of this relevant and not discriminatory?! 



**Colonel Bowe:** It could be relevant if he’s the result of some twisted Nazi engineering. An imperfect Nazi weapon to topple us from the inside. Too late to save them, but just in time to sow chaos. Or maybe he's a member of the Serpent’s Hand? Or maybe he's some otherworldly anomalous force looking to ingratiate and plant himself in our midst to bring about the GOCs end. An imperfect infiltrator. Maybe he’s a shapeshifter desperate for attention who got lucky on some predictions. A shapeshifter that molded himself into what he thinks a Norn would look like to prevent being gassed and burnt to death by Nazis. A very good liar, but an imperfect imitator. Imperfect in all ways because he can’t remove the deepest truth about himself.



//PTE-001 flinches and then sits motionless.//



**Colonel Bowe:** Can you shapeshift PTE-001? 



**PTE-001:** N-n-no. I--I don't know. 



**Colonel Bowe:** See! Even he doesn't know if he can! Why don't you try, right now, for all of us? 



//One minute passes in silence with all parties looking at PTE-001. Nothing happens. PTE-001’s face is pale.//



**PTE-001:** I can't.



**Colonel Bowe:** You can't, or you won't? Won't because it will result in your immediate liquidation!?



//One of the Committee Members bangs their gavel as the room erupts into shouts.//



**Unnamed Committee Member:** That’s enough! Quiet, all of you or I will have you removed. Colonel, this has veered into the realm of thinly veiled speculative fiction. Keep your questions focused on the evidence we have. 



**Colonel Bowe:** I’m simply addressing what the whole Committee was thinking about him. But I think I’ve hammered home my point enough, let’s move on.



//Colonel Bowe shuffles a stack of papers for several seconds.//



**Colonel Bowe:** PTE-001, How old would you say you are? 



//PTE-001 spends several seconds staring at the table. It rocks backwards and forwards in the seat. Colonel Bowe repeats the question. PTE-001 sits up straight and speaks in an abruptly raised voice, slamming the butt of the staff against the ground. Multiple members of the Cult’s delegation and the Committee jump or flinch. Several guards shift closer to the Committee.//



**PTE-001:** Too old. Old enough to remember the world aflame, the sky torn asunder with bleeding light, and the great battle drums hammering against a raging sea. Older than I should be, should have ever been, younger than I will be when the sky fills with the lights of a place and time reborn. When the thunder of creation shall begin its ascent once more to the hateful stars.



//PTE-001 sags back down in its chair, shaking vigorously. Several seconds of whispered silence.//  



**PTE-001:** I am old. Very old. 



//Several more seconds of silence. Colonel Bowe taps a pen on the podium.// 



**Colonel Bowe:** Can you give us an exact age?



//PTE-001 shakes its head. It begins rocking back and forth again.//



**Colonel Bowe:** Please state your response into the microphone, PTE-001.



**PTE-001:** No.



**Colonel Bowe:** Moving on then. Obskurakorps records are few and far between when it comes to you, PTE-001. You were mistaken for a [Slur Removed][[footnote]]The slur in context is a term used for Romani.[[/footnote]]?



//PTE-001 places one hand on the side of her head, staring down at the table. It shakes for several seconds before answering.//



**PTE-001:** Yes. 



**Colonel Bowe:** Was that the real reason they took you to the concentration camps? Or was it because you’re actually a deluded, shapeshifting transvestite?



//PTE-001 breathes heavily into the microphone.//



**PTE-001:** No it wasn’—it was because they believed me Romani.  I’ve seen what they did, again and again. So many lost to gas, bodies rendered ash and hastily buried in the ground. Children screaming for their mothers, families pulled apart, men shot and beaten and lost to time and reason. 



//PTE-001 breaks down into heavy sobs. A brief thirty-minute intermission occurs at the Cult of the Nornir’s request. Upon returning, PTE-001 is more composed. When the Committee reenters, Colonel Bowe’s face is red and he is frowning.// 



**Unnamed Committee Member:** For the record, before we resume, let’s hold a moment of silence for all those lost to Nazi cruelty. 



//One minute of silence.//



**Colonel Bowe:** These questions might be difficult for you, but we must ask them. Where did the Obskurakorps capture you?



//PTE-001 starts and stops speaking several times.//



**PTE-001:** Outside a sacred place that cannot be spoken of to the whispers of the mortal world for they will drown its pools in blood and leave it barren. A fate repeating again and again and failed to be stopped. Always failed, always binding an innocent other to an arduous path. 



//Several seconds of whispers. PTE-001 breathes heavily into the microphone, releases its staff and rubs its face.//



**Unnamed Committee member:** She’s telling the truth, Bowe.



//Colonel Bowe’s frown deepens. He looks towards the Committee member, opens his mouth, closes it, and then looks back to PTE-001.//



**Colonel Bowe:** Can you give the Committee an exact location?



//PTE-001’s voice cracks.//



**PTE-001:** No.



//Colonel Bowe rubs his brow.//



**Colonel Bowe:** Even if we are already aware of the Well of Urd and the roots of Yggdrasil?



**PTE-001:** The answer would not change. 



//Colonel Bowe’s frown deepens. He looks down at his podium.// 



**Colonel Bowe:** You’re not exactly giving the Committee much trust in your willingness to cooperate, PTE-001. 



//PTE-001 does not respond. It has begun biting its bottom lip.// 



 **Colonel Bowe:** Here, I’ll throw you an easy question. What is your name? You should be able to answer at least that. 



//PTE-001’s head tilts up from the table and stares in the general direction of Colonel Bowe.//



**PTE-001:** Many different things to many people. She Who Saw the End, the Mad Storyteller, The Blind Wanderer, Bringer of Doom, Twister of Fate, Sister of the Damned. 



//Colonel Bowe clenches his fist against the podium with each additional title.//



**Colonel Bowe:** And what about your given name, the one you use to describe yourself? Surely you have one of those you can tell us? One of the Norn ones? Or maybe you had different names for yourself. Or is it Tiresias? An Oracle? One of the Moirai? Something surely?



//PTE-001 sits up and speaks louder with more confidence.//



**PTE-001:** A true name has power. Holds sway in the minds of those who seize it. It was spoken many times, long ago, but… now it is spoken only in history and whispers in games of fiction and myth. I prefer it that way. It’s better that way. It shouldn’t be spoken elsewhere, not to mortals like you, not to the masses who would wash in it. If you seek a title to properly refer to me, Seeress will do. 



//Colonel Bowe rubs the bridge of his nose.//



**Colonel Bowe:** I am asking you a simple fucking question. Either you give me a proper answer, or you don’t have one. //Who the fuck are you? What is your given name placed on you at birth?//



**Unnamed Committee Member:** Language, Colonel.



**PTE-001:** I cannot tell you that, because I have none that I recognize as mine in your eyes. You look for something that cannot be given to you. Something you wouldn’t believe if told. Only to a few who remain will it be believed. 



//Colonel Bowe throws his hands up and then bangs one fist on the podium.//



**Colonel Bowe:** How are we supposed to trust you when all you do is run in circles around us verbally with this cryptic speech?



**PTE-001:** Trust is earned. 



//Colonel Bowe growls. PTE-001 is sitting up straight, both hands holding the staff.//



**Colonel Bowe:** Who are those few who remain?



**PTE-001:** In time they shall reveal themselves to you without ever knowing their connections, yet against you they’ll remain until it ends in flame and red-lines. They will stand against your children and children’s children onwards everlasting. And you? Black dripping from your flesh, feathers fluttering in the air and screams. 



//Colonel Bowe sighs and holds his hands up in the air.//



**Colonel Bowe:** Well, this is getting nowhere. It seems he both knows everything yet knows nothing and can say nothing of worth at the same time. 



**PTE-001:** There is one thing I know of that I can speak about. 



**Colonel Bowe:** Enlighten us, please.



**PTE-001:** You are wearing a black tie, a blue navy jacket and straight legged pants that are slightly too large; bought when you were twenty pounds heavier. Your hair is gelled back and dyed to compensate for the grey spreading on your scalp. Your shoes are too tight. Most discomforting, your stomach is still aching from a particularly ancient sausage you had this morning. A deep longing insecurity burns in your belly for something you don’t understand. In another life, you may have seen it, your grandchild certainly will. 



//Several seconds of silence, followed by whispers and then light applause. Colonel Bowe stares at PTE-001. PTE-001 stares back.//



**Colonel Bowe:** How did you know all that?



**PTE-001:** I can see it in the way you’re squirming in that chair, obviously. 



**Colonel Bowe:** But you’re blind. 



**PTE-001:** Yes, thank you for explaining the joke. I can read it off the transcriber’s paper again if you like?



//General Bowe frowns and narrows his eyes while the rest of the room descends into several seconds of chuckling.//



//Colonel Bowe leans forward over the podium and speaks aggressively.//



**Colonel Bowe:** PTE-001, you were moved from a Nazi Concentration camp shortly after Obskurakorps discovered your self-claimed prophetic occultic properties. Were you ever an Obskurakorps collaborator?



//Several of the speakers make as if to stand or shout while baring teeth. They are stopped by other members of the delegation. PTE-001 flinches at the question. Its mouth is open, and it shrinks into the chair.//



**PTE-001:** No! I would sooner throw myself into the sea to be killed at the hands of a kraken. Those monsters did unspeakable things to me!



**Colonel Bowe:** But you did assist Obskurakorps forces with the use of your ‘claimed’ prophetic occultic properties, didn’t you? Did they promise you fulfillment for your sick and twisted sexual fantasies if you cooperated?



//PTE-001 begins rocking back and forth while shaking vigorously.//



**Speaker Ella:** I must object! Colonel, you have read the reports of the condition she was found in. It wasn’t assistance, it was coercion! 



**Colonel Bowe:** That’s precisely my point, Speaker Ella! PTE-001 claims he was coerced into providing assistance to the Obskurakorps and the Nazi regime. What’s stopping that from happening again in the hands of one of our enemies? 



**Speaker Ella:** Nothing right now, but if the GOC gives her adequate protection and lets us assist her in her divine duties with little interference, it should never be an issue. 



**Colonel Bowe:** But the possibility remains nonetheless, no?



//Speaker Ella hesitates for several seconds.//



**Speaker Ella:** We can’t completely rule it out. 



**Colonel Bowe:** What if he’s lying and we’re letting a wolf in sheep’s clothing through the door? 



//Speaker Ella hesitates again.//



**Speaker Ella:** She would have done an incredible job in fooling us all. 



**Colonel Bowe:** That’s what I thought. 



//Colonel Bowe turns right then left looking at the rest of the Committee.//



**Colonel Bowe:** My peers, the fact that this anomaly can be forced to assist another party means it is a threat, just one that isn’t active right now. At least while he remains under our thumb. But who’s to say how long that lasts? Who’s to say he won’t turn on us internally? Important thing to remember and develop countermeasures for. If it’s of any benefit to us, assuming its prophetic occultic properties are even real. But let’s face reality for a minute. The fact that //it// refuses to tell us its real name, its age, and where it even came from throws serious doubt on whether it is actually prescient or even a Norn. Furthermore, the fact that it is a he, and not a she, as so many of you seem to be defaulting to, is indicative to me that he cannot be a Norn. We have photos!  



//Colonel Bowe holds up medical photographs of PTE-001’s anatomy.//



**Colonel Bowe:** We must stop playing along with the mental derangement of this clearly, extremely ill man. He is in need of desperate assistance in an asylum for the anomalous where he cannot threaten our global mandate. And if that is not enough to stymy the potential threat, then liquidation is our only option. 



//Several seconds of raised voices and exchanges rendered unintelligible by the number of people speaking or shouting. A gavel is heard banging.//



**Unnamed Committee Member:** We will come to order! 



//All yelling stops as the gavel banging continues. An unidentified committee member speaks with a layered thaumic voice modulation.//



**Unidentified Committee Member:** Thank you, Colonel Bowe, for proselytizing on the nature of the entity. I’ll remind you that this isn’t a military court, it’s a committee tribunal.  This discussion is for the Committee to have behind closed doors, and you know this. And for the last time, stop dragging your frankly disgustingly primitive American perspective on women into official matters. 



//The unidentified committee member sighs for several seconds.//



**Unidentified Committee Member:** Now then. I’ll remind the Cult of the Nornir that this is a tribunal, and that we will not tolerate such outbursts again. I am not afraid of having you all dragged out of this room kicking and screaming. Please take your seats and let’s move forward to the second part of our assessment. 



//Colonel Bowe’s cheeks redden and he sits. Speaker Ella places a hand on PTE-001’s shoulder. The latter is still shaking and has its head in its hands.//



**Unnamed Committee Member:** Speaker Ella, does the entity require another short recess?



//Several minutes pass where Speaker Ella and Speaker Edvard are quietly whispering to PTE-001.//



//PTE-001 slowly sits up and removes its hands.//



**Speaker Ella:** The Seeress is ready to continue, Ma’am. 



//The Committee member nods their head.//



**Unnamed Committee Member:** Speaker Ella, would you please state, for the record, PTE-001’s occultic properties as you best understand them?



//Speaker Ella stands.//



**Speaker Ella:** The Seeress possesses powerful precognition, prescience, and sight affliction which are random and uncontrolled. It’s our understanding she can actively control them, at physical cost to herself. 



//Several seconds of whispers from the Committee. Colonel Bowe both appears skeptical and rolls his eyes.//



**Speaker Ella:** She also is blessed with an abnormal healing ability. We believe, after some discussion, she is immortal and much older than she appears.



**Unknown Committee Member:** That seems clear by the earlier exchanges. Do you have any idea how old?



**Speaker Ella:** She has not been more forthcoming with us than she has with the Committee. But by my best estimation, thousands of years old.   



**Unknown Committee Member:** Alternatively, if she is as powerful in prescience as claimed, she may see far into the past, giving the misleading impression of being older than she is. Regardless, let’s move on. Of these properties, which does the Cult of the Nornir believe to be most beneficial to the GOC?



**Speaker Ella:** Her prescience, ma’am. 



**Unknown Committee Member:** Sensible. Thank you, Speaker Ella. 



//Speaker Ella sits and the Committee turns their attention back to PTE-001.//



**Unknown Committee Member:** “PTE-001, we are going to ask you to demonstrate your prescience. Are you capable of doing so at this time?”



//PTE-001 stands slowly, shaking and hesitates before speaking.//



**PTE-001:** I will do what’s needed. 



//The Committee members nod. Colonel Bowe crosses their arms.//



**Unknown Committee Member:** Cooperation is good. We’ll start with simple demonstrations of predictions based on probability. 



**Colonel Bowe:** You can’t be serious; probability tests can be easily gamed. 



**Unknown  Committee Member:** Do you have a better suggestion, Colonel? 



**Colonel Bowe:** Have him predict major world events for the next year, like we discussed beforehand.



**Unknown Committee Member:** Would a simple probability test not be an effective screen so that we don’t waste our time further? 



//Colonel Bowe snorts loudly.//



**Colonel Bowe:** If you want to waste more time, then go ahead I suppose. 



**Unknown Committee Member:** Your flippancy is unwarranted, Colonel. That said, objections are noted. 



//PTE-001 is asked to identify the outcome of twelve individual coinflips and eight dice rolls. It is then asked to predict cards drawn from a deck nine times. It accurately predicts all events.// 



**Unknown Committee Member:** We appreciate your cooperation, PTE-001. That was… impressive.



//The other committee members nod in agreement while Colonel Bowe curls his lips back and rolls his eyes.//



**Unknown Committee Member:** Now that the simple tasks are out of the way, we would ask you to predict as many major events that will occur this year as you can. To the best of your ability, of course. We will track how many of these predictions come to pass, though not necessarily the granular detail at this stage. After one year, we will evaluate all your predictions and conclude this meeting. This seems a long time, but you will be allowed to remain in the care and custody of the Cult of the Nornir while being made accessible to us as needed. You may take your time in making these predictions, but we will all remain in this room until they are finished.



**PTE-001:** It is a very short time in the great sweeping tides of life. I will do my best. 



//Several seconds of silence as the committee members watch PTE-001. The entity sways while leaning against its staff.//



**PTE-001:** May I make a request for some items to assist me?



//Several seconds of murmuring.//



**Unknown Committee Member:** It’s unusual, but we’ll entertain it if you can explain why you need specific items.



**PTE-001:** Whatever is necessary.



**Unknown Committee Member:** Go ahead then.



//PTE-001 sways again for several seconds before speaking.//



**PTE-001:** May I have a glass of chocolate milk, some water, soda, candy, a sandwich with roast beef, and a bucket.



**Unknown Committee Member:** …why the chocolate milk?



**PTE-001:** Chocolate milk helps the temporal strand headaches. 



**Unknown Committee Member:** And the roast beef sandwich and bucket?



**PTE-001:** The roast beef is for iron to replenish lost blood. The bucket is for vomit.



//Several seconds of whispers. Colonel Bowe frowns, appearing incredulous.//



**Unknown Committee Member:** Well, not the strangest explanations I’ve heard in my tenure. Would one of the assistants please retrieve those items?



[Idle conversation removed for brevity]



**Unknown Committee Member:** You may begin at your convenience, PTE-001.



//Instead of a single glass of chocolate milk, PTE-001 has been given an entire pitcher. Colonel Bowe is apoplectic.// 



//PTE-001 grips its staff tight, sitting up straight in the chair. Its voice becomes layered in the audio recording, commanding attention similar to an audio-hazard but with no observable lasting effects. The lights in the room begin to flicker.// 



**PTE-001:** In a land once swept by Immortals and grand emperors of Xerxes and Darius, the earth shall split in the North beneath the bend of hammer and sickle and a man of steel’s resolve. The land will bleed, the valley shall burn, and a red tide shall break at the whims of an eagle balding beneath a branching globe.





