**Summary of Predictive Outcome:** Iran Crisis 1946



[[include <a href="/component:image-block">component:image-block</a> name=https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/bleep-s-onyx-proposal/Kurdistan_republic_mahabad.webp|align=left|caption=Separatists during the Iran Crisis of 1946.]]



On 21st November, 1945, the regions of Iranian Azerbaijani and Mahabad seceded from the Iranian state after the end of World War II. British and Soviet forces had invaded Iran during the war to secure supply lines to support the Soviet war machine. Joseph Stalin refused to relinquish influence over these regions following the end of hostilities. 



Pressure from the United States at the UN and through material assistance to Iran eventually forced the Soviet Union to withdraw support. Iranian troops stormed both breakaway regions and retook them over the course of late 1946 and early 1947. An estimated 2000 people have died as of June 1947.



**Predictive Assessment as of January 2nd, 1947:** Though vague and somewhat cryptic, PTE-001 predicted the event and outcome. 



